For the technical interview for Java, please prepare the following topics:
1.	Java OOP concepts
o	Constructors in detail - what and why, constructor chaining
o	Static keyword in detail - Static method, static block, overriding static methods
o	Final keyword usage with examples
o	Java Inheritance
o	Java Polymorphism - Runtime Polymorphism, Static and Dynamic binding – How do we implement
o	Encapsulation – How do we implement
o	Abstraction
o	Aggregation and Composition
o	Access modifiers in Java
•	Exception Handling - Exception propagation in Java, Checked and Unchecked exception, throws and throw keywords, finally keyword, try with resources, difference between error and exception, custom exceptions
•	Java Multithreading
o	Thread LifeCycle
o	Executor framework
o	Future Object, CompletableFuture
•	Functional Interfaces - Detailed understanding, Types of functional interfaces (Consumer, Predicate, Supplier) and why these are important. Should be able to write code for that 
•	Stream API - Hands on programming using Stream API, Should be able to write programs using Stream API – Intermediate and Terminal functions
•	Synchronization in Java
•	Collections - Detailed understanding, Internal working of hashmap, equals and hashcode method usage
•	Java 8 new features, Java 11 new features, Java 17 new features.
•	Lambda function - Should be able to write program
•	Springboot
o	Dependency Injection (DI) and Inversion of Control (IoC): Understand how Spring manages beans and their dependencies.
o	Annotations: Familiarize yourself with annotations like @Component, @Service, @Repository, @Configuration, @Autowired, @Value, etc.
o	Bean Scopes: Understand singleton, prototype, request, and session scopes.
o	Profiles: Learn how to activate different configurations based on environments.
•	SOLID Principle – Along with coding examples
•	Spring Security – Authentication/ Authorization, JWT Token, How to secure your applications
•	Microservices – Coupling and Cohesion, Microservice Design Patterns – Eg. Circuit Breaker, Saga Pattern, Orchestration and Choreography
•	REST API – HTTP methods – get, put, post, patch, delete
•	Maven Lifecycle
•	Spring Bean Lifecycle
•	Concurrent/Parallel programming
•	String class 
String test = “” vs String test = new String()
String immutability
.equals vs ==
•	Class Immutibility, Comparator, Comparable.
•	Design Patterns
Singleton/Factory
•	SQL query – Should be able to write queries with aggregate functions – RANK, DENSE_RANK
•	Memory management – Understanding to heap and stack memory, garbage collections (Java 8 and Java 17), Analysis of Java heap dump, Tools used for analysing, how do you handle memory exception
•	Performance handling – How to approach
•	Swagger Open API, Postman
•	Hibernate or any ORM tool – Details about it – 1st Level Cache, 2nd level Cache
•	Out of memory exception – How do you handle
•	CI/CD, Devops
•	Unix Shell Commands
•	

